					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-472750#post-4383309</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-472750/scp-1333#post-4383309</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 01 Oct 2019 10:21:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doc Rot</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5653603</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm fairly on the fence about this one. The article is pretty well written but the concept just doesn't interest me that much. It's possibly due to the fact that some modern malware makes this look quite tame. I also strongly agree that this should be Euclid as there are multiple instances of this scip loose in the wild and it self replicates and spreads like wildfire. No vote from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
